## Introduction
Atmospheric water is water that is produced or collected from the air (atmosphere) in the form of vapor, clouds, or moisture.
## Working Principle
Evaporation – Water from rivers, lakes becomes vapor
Condensation – Vapor cools and forms clouds
Precipitation – Water falls back to Earth
## Methods Used
Atmospheric Water Generator (AWG):
Device that extracts water from air humidity
Works by cooling air → condensing vapor → collecting water
## Advantages
Provides water in water-scarce regions
Uses natural humidity
Eco-friendly source
## Limitations
Works well only in high humidity
In dry areas (deserts), water production is very low ❌
## Future Scope
Can provide drinking water in dry and rural regions
Helpful where groundwater is limited
